{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":929,"text":"I am multidisciplinary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2816,"text":"As a scientist, I've been a crew commander\nfor a NASA Mars simulation last year,"},{"time":7799,"text":"and as an artist, I create multicultural\ncommunity art all over the planet."},{"time":14718,"text":"And recently, I've actually\nbeen combining both."},{"time":17622,"text":"But let me first talk a little more\nabout that NASA mission."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21337,"text":"This is the HI-SEAS program."},{"time":23240,"text":"HI-SEAS is a NASA-funded\nplanetary surface analogue"},{"time":26936,"text":"on the Mauna Loa volcano in Hawaii,"},{"time":29664,"text":"and it's a research program\nthat is specifically designed"},{"time":32690,"text":"to study the effects\nof long-term isolation of small crews."},{"time":37729,"text":"I lived in this dome for four months\nwith a crew of six,"},{"time":41601,"text":"a very interesting experience, of course."},{"time":44386,"text":"We did all kinds of research."},{"time":47469,"text":"Our main research\nwas actually a food study,"},{"time":49821,"text":"but apart from that food study --"},{"time":51700,"text":"developing a new food system\nfor astronauts living in deep space --"},{"time":55488,"text":"we also did all kinds of other research."},{"time":57621,"text":"We did extra-vehicular activities,\nas you can see here,"},{"time":60942,"text":"wearing mock-up space suits,"},{"time":62986,"text":"but we also had our chores\nand lots of other stuff to do,"},{"time":65655,"text":"like questionnaires\nat the end of every day."},{"time":67907,"text":"Busy, busy work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69700,"text":"Now, as you can imagine,"},{"time":71752,"text":"it's quite challenging to live\nwith just a small group of people"},{"time":74804,"text":"in a small space for a long time."},{"time":76987,"text":"There's all kinds\nof psychological challenges:"},{"time":79216,"text":"how to keep a team together\nin these circumstances;"},{"time":83092,"text":"how to deal with the warping of time\nyou start to sense"},{"time":85822,"text":"when you're living in these circumstances;"},{"time":88015,"text":"sleep problems that arise; etc."},{"time":89949,"text":"But also we learned a lot."},{"time":92033,"text":"I learned a lot about\nhow individual crew members"},{"time":94749,"text":"actually cope with a situation like this;"},{"time":97419,"text":"how you can keep a crew\nproductive and happy,"},{"time":100926,"text":"for example, giving them\na good deal of autonomy"},{"time":103526,"text":"is a good trick to do that;"},{"time":105058,"text":"and honestly, I learned\na lot about leadership,"},{"time":108047,"text":"because I was a crew commander."}]},{"cues":[{"time":109935,"text":"So doing this mission,"},{"time":111839,"text":"I really started thinking more deeply\nabout our future in outer space."},{"time":116725,"text":"We will venture into outer space,\nand we will start inhabiting outer space."},{"time":120394,"text":"I have no doubt about it."},{"time":122159,"text":"It might take 50 years\nor it might take 500 years,"},{"time":125744,"text":"but it's going to happen nevertheless."},{"time":128443,"text":"So I came up with\na new art project called Seeker."},{"time":132434,"text":"And the Seeker project is actually\nchallenging communities all over the world"},{"time":136355,"text":"to come up with starship prototypes"},{"time":139209,"text":"that re-envision\nhuman habitation and survival."},{"time":142513,"text":"That's the core of the project."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144382,"text":"Now, one important thing:"},{"time":146739,"text":"This is not a dystopian project."},{"time":149244,"text":"This is not about, \"Oh my God,\nthe world is going wrong"},{"time":151956,"text":"and we have to escape because we need\nanother future somewhere else.\""},{"time":155218,"text":"No, no."},{"time":157029,"text":"The project is basically inviting people"},{"time":159696,"text":"to take a step away\nfrom earthbound constraints"},{"time":162661,"text":"and, as such, reimagine our future."},{"time":165319,"text":"And it's really helpful,\nand it works really well,"},{"time":168003,"text":"so that's really the important part\nof what we're doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172260,"text":"Now, in this project,\nI'm using a cocreation approach,"},{"time":176988,"text":"which is a slightly different approach"},{"time":179078,"text":"from what you would expect\nfrom many artists."},{"time":181580,"text":"I'm essentially dropping a basic idea\ninto a group, into a community,"},{"time":185963,"text":"people start gravitating to the idea,"},{"time":188491,"text":"and together, we shape \nand build the artwork."},{"time":191851,"text":"It's a little bit like termites, really."},{"time":194018,"text":"We just work together,"},{"time":195308,"text":"and even, for example,\nwhen architects visit what we're doing,"},{"time":198264,"text":"sometimes they have a bit\nof a hard time understanding"},{"time":200849,"text":"how we build without a master plan."},{"time":202527,"text":"We always come up with these\nfantastic large-scale scupltures"},{"time":205986,"text":"that actually we can also inhabit."},{"time":209678,"text":"The first version was done\nin Belgium and Holland."},{"time":213022,"text":"It was built with a team\nof almost 50 people."},{"time":215924,"text":"This is the second iteration\nof that same project,"},{"time":218785,"text":"but in Slovenia, in a different country,"},{"time":220745,"text":"and the new group was like, we're going \nto do the architecture differently."},{"time":224987,"text":"So they took away the architecture,\nthey kept the base of the artwork,"},{"time":228291,"text":"and they built an entirely new,"},{"time":230343,"text":"much more biomorphic\narchitecture on top of that."},{"time":233014,"text":"And that's another\ncrucial part of the project."},{"time":235429,"text":"It's an evolving artwork,\nevolving architecture."},{"time":239310,"text":"This was the last version that was just\npresented a few weeks ago in Holland,"},{"time":243137,"text":"which was using caravans \nas modules to build a starship."},{"time":247282,"text":"We bought some second-hand caravans,"},{"time":249308,"text":"cut them open,"},{"time":250605,"text":"and reassembled them into a starship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253342,"text":"Now, when we're thinking about starships,"},{"time":256249,"text":"we're not just approaching it\nas a technological challenge."},{"time":259287,"text":"We're really looking at it\nas a combination of three systems:"},{"time":262215,"text":"ecology, people and technology."},{"time":264596,"text":"So there's always a strong ecological\ncomponent in the project."},{"time":268154,"text":"Here you can see aquaponic systems"},{"time":270523,"text":"that are actually\nsurrounding the astronauts,"},{"time":272727,"text":"so they're constantly in contact\nwith part of the food that they're eating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278659,"text":"Now, a very typical thing for this project"},{"time":281695,"text":"is that we run our own isolation missions\ninside these art and design projects."},{"time":288773,"text":"We actually lock ourselves up\nfor multiple days on end,"},{"time":291747,"text":"and test what we build."},{"time":293447,"text":"And this is, for example,"},{"time":294875,"text":"on the right hand side\nyou can see an isolation mission"},{"time":297489,"text":"in the Museum of Modern Art\nin Ljubljana in Slovenia,"},{"time":300407,"text":"where six artists and designers\nlocked themselves up --"},{"time":303025,"text":"I was part of that --"},{"time":304935,"text":"for four days inside the museum."},{"time":307173,"text":"And, of course, obviously,\nthis is a very performative"},{"time":309928,"text":"and very strong experience for all of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314130,"text":"Now, the next version of the project\nis currently being developed"},{"time":318549,"text":"together with Camilo Rodriguez-Beltran,\nwho is also a TED Fellow,"},{"time":322512,"text":"in the Atacama Desert in Chile,\na magical place."},{"time":326788,"text":"First of all, it's really\nconsidered a Mars analogue."},{"time":329896,"text":"It really does look like Mars\nin certain locations"},{"time":332590,"text":"and has been used by NASA\nto test equipment."},{"time":336119,"text":"And it has a long history\nof being connected to space"},{"time":339222,"text":"through observations of the stars."},{"time":341977,"text":"It's now home to ALMA,"},{"time":343645,"text":"the large telescope\nthat's being developed there."},{"time":347183,"text":"But also, it's the driest\nlocation on the planet,"},{"time":351143,"text":"and that makes it extremely interesting\nto build our project,"},{"time":354144,"text":"because suddenly, sustainability\nis something we have to explore fully."},{"time":359829,"text":"We have no other option,"},{"time":361661,"text":"so I'm very curious to see\nwhat's going to happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364074,"text":"Now, a specific thing for this\nparticular version of the project"},{"time":368231,"text":"is that I'm very interested to see"},{"time":370413,"text":"how we can connect\nwith the local population,"},{"time":372569,"text":"the native population."},{"time":373802,"text":"These people have been living there\nfor a very long time"},{"time":376544,"text":"and can be considered\nexperts in sustainability,"},{"time":379516,"text":"and so I'm very interested\nto see what we can learn from them,"},{"time":382487,"text":"and have an input of indigenous knowledge\ninto space exploration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386719,"text":"So we're trying to redefine\nhow we look at our future in outer space"},{"time":391598,"text":"by exploring integration,\nbiology, technology and people;"},{"time":396002,"text":"by using a cocreation approach;"},{"time":398652,"text":"and by using and exploring\nlocal traditions"},{"time":402099,"text":"and to see how we can learn from the past\nand integrate that into our deep future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406528,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408321,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}